  "prompt": "What is needed to become a yoga teacher?",
  "response": "To become a yoga teacher, you typically need:\n\n1. Yoga Training and Certification\n- Complete a Yoga Teacher Training (YTT) program\n- Most programs require 200 hours of training\n- Some advanced certifications offer 500-hour programs\n\n2. Personal Yoga Practice\n- Extensive personal experience with yoga\n- Proficiency in various yoga styles and techniques\n- Strong understanding of yoga philosophy\n\n3. Physical Requirements\n- Good overall fitness\n- Flexibility\n- Strong understanding of body mechanics\n\n4. Education\n- High school diploma or equivalent\n- Some programs prefer some college education\n\n5. Specific Skills\n- Strong communication abilities\n- Patience\n- Ability to demonstrate and explain poses\n- Teaching and interpersonal skills\n\n6. Certification/Registration\n- Register with Yoga Alliance or similar professional organization\n- Obtain liability insurance\n- Some states may require additional credentials\n\n7. Optional but Beneficial\n- Additional specialized training (e.g., prenatal, kids' yoga)\n- Background in anatomy, fitness, or health sciences\n- First aid/CPR certification\n\n8. Continuing Education\n- Regular workshops\n- Advanced trainings\n- Staying updated on yoga techniques and research\n\nCosts can range from $1,000-$3,000 for initial training, depending on the program.",
